pamela rose presents wild women of song events at stanford pamela rose presents wild women of song facebook twitter email print add to calendar bay area jazz and blues singer pamela rose makes a compelling and swinging case for the enduring contributions of women to american's treasure trove of popular music from alberta hunter to peggy lee she brings this message home in this engaging multimedia stage show where images photos songs and storytelling are supported by the first rate musicianship of sjw faculty tammy hall ruth davies and kristen strom boasting a rich bold voice and a swinging soulful style pamela rose is that rare breed of entertainer who connects solidly with her audience by always delivering a personal and unforgettable musical experience according to the san francisco chronicle rose shines a light on the words and music of female composers the result is a show that is pure entertainment and a delightful romp through the history of the jazz age when wednesday july 20 2011 7 30 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where dinkelspiel auditorium 471 lagunita dr stanford ca 94305 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags performance music arts sponsor stanford jazz workshop contact 736 0324 info stanfordjazz org admission tickets $28 general $18 students stanford ticket office 650 725 arts 2787 http tickets stanford edu permalink http events stanford edu events 279 27969 more info last modified july 11 2011
